Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: Confucian Ways
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00bvz8s
Last Broadcast Date: Sat 7 Jun 2008
Chinese Vistas: In a lecture recorded at the British Library in London, Jonathan Spence reflects on China's most enduring thinker, Confucius. Who was this man, what did he believe in, and what contemporary relevance does his message have, nearly 2,500 years after his death? The Confucian message has survived countless attacks and is being recycled by the Chinese Communist leadership today. Show less